&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rules to behave properly online&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;key-points&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Key Points&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Key Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Netiquette&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the set of rules and guidelines that dictate acceptable behavior and manners when communicating and interacting online.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These rules help maintain a respectful and courteous environment on the internet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Netiquette covers various aspects of online behavior, including email etiquette, social media conduct, and forum participation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adhering to netiquette helps prevent misunderstandings, conflicts, and the spread of misinformation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Common netiquette guidelines include avoiding all caps (which can be perceived as shouting), being mindful of tone, and respecting others&amp;#39; privacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;additional-info&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Additional Information&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Additional Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Netiquette also involves being considerate of others&amp;#39; time and bandwidth, by avoiding sending large attachments or long, unnecessary messages.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It encourages the use of appropriate language and discourages the use of offensive or inflammatory remarks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Netiquette promotes the idea of thinking before posting and considering the potential impact of one&amp;#39;s words and actions online.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As the internet continues to evolve, so do the rules of netiquette, adapting to new forms of digital communication and social interaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
